This is quite an ugly, manipulative one isn't it? It preys on this classic masculine fear of abandonment in a tremendously disgusting way. What therapy could fix something like this?

What happens when someone with no prior romantic attachments comes in contact with it? Presumably it 'hunts' vulnerable males (i.e. those still grieving, perhaps unconsciously, previous mates), but it might have to prey on pubescent humans if it has a lack of plausible prey. Would it then appear as a formerly unobtainable middle/high school crush? A sexual fantasy, a la playboy model?

Really creepy, an emotionally manipulative predator.

+1

Criticism: sometimes i dislike the 'this item's abilities will corrupt Foundation staff' arrangement, especially regards all personnel entering wearing opague goggles. Presumably if all personnel involved in its containment were properly briefed, the buddy system would be safer and more efficient - or two janitorial staff accompanied by two armed guards. (Let's assume for the sake of realism these personnel have other duties that fill the other 7.5 hours of the workday.) Does this thing eat, anyhow?





